nib.text:
An armed man who allegedly started a fire after barricading himself inside an apartment was arrested early Thursday morning in the North End, police said.

At 1:26 a.m., police responded to a report that a man was trespassing in an apartment near Marion Street and Wheelock Parkway West. 

The man left the apartment, but returned an hour later, according to a report from [KSTP](https://kstp.com/kstp-news/local-news/overnight-fire-damages-st-paul-apartment/). 

Police responded to the scene and escorted a woman out of the apartment safely. 

The man, who was armed with a knife, then barricaded himself inside a bedroom and made multiple verbal threats, including that he would burn down the building, police told local news reporters. 

As officers attempted to make contact with him, they observed smoke coming from the bedroom. 

Eventually, the man complied with officers' requests to exit the apartment and drop his knife. 

He was arrested for arson and the violation of a protection order, according to local news reports. 

Police evacuated the building as firefighters responded to the scene and began to put out the flames. 

Citizen user videos captured massive flames and plumes of smoke coming from multiple floors of the building. 

Residents were directed to heated Metro Transit buses, in addition to nearby apartments and other vehicles. 

The Red Cross also responded to the scene to assist displaced residents. 

Radio transmissions from the scene indicated two dogs were rescued from the building. Both were picked up by animal control as firefighters could not locate their owners.   

At 3:49 a.m., crews reported the fire had been extinguished. 

No injuries were reported.
